# <repo-name> Agent Route

Read `README.md` first for repository purpose and entry points.

## Route

- For repository-native docs placement, read `Docs/README.md` before editing.
- For current canonical structure, read `Docs/Architecture/README.md` and the
  relevant architecture files.
- For design-in-progress, use `Docs/Proposals/*` when that subtree is present.
- For change history, consult `Docs/Decisions/*`, `Docs/Migrations/*`, and
  `Docs/Archive/*` when those subtrees are present.
- For GitHub-facing collaboration files, use `.github/` and root governance
  files.
- Stop and clarify before mixing route instructions into `README` files or
  index text into `AGENTS.md`.

## Authority

- `AGENTS.md` routes work.
- `README`-class files index scope and placement.
- `Docs/Architecture/*` is current truth.
- `Docs/Proposals/*` is proposal space when that subtree is present.
- `Docs/Decisions/*`, `Docs/Migrations/*`, and `Docs/Archive/*` are history
  when those subtrees are present.
- `.github/*` is GitHub-facing governance.

## Operating Notes

- Keep Route and Index separate.
- Keep current truth out of proposal and history subtrees when they are
  present.
- Keep GitHub collaboration configuration out of `Docs/`.
